com.google.appengine.api.channel

Class ChannelMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.appengine.api.channel.ChannelMessage

  • public final class ChannelMessage
extends java.lang.Object
    Class that represents a channel message. ChannelMessages can be sent as outgoing messages or can be parsed as incoming messages by ChannelService.parseMessage(HttpServletRequest).

    • Constructor Detail

      • ChannelMessage

        public ChannelMessage(java.lang.String clientId,
              java.lang.String message)
        Constructor for a channel message.
        Parameters:
        clientId - identifies the client that will receive this message. The client should be connected to the channel using a token created by ChannelService.CreateChannel, using the same client id. The client id must be fewer than 64 bytes when encoded to UTF-8.
        message - the message payload. The payload must be smaller than 32K when encoded to UTF-8.
